# AKS Module

This Terraform module creates Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS) clusters, node pools, and related resources for both development and production environments.

## Features

- ✅ **AKS Cluster** - Create AKS with configurable networking and security settings
- ✅ **System and User Node Pools** - Manage default and additional node pools
- ✅ **Private Cluster** - Enable private API endpoint and authorized IP ranges
- ✅ **OIDC Issuer** - Enable OIDC for workload identity integration
- ✅ **AKS Add-ons** - Azure Policy, Key Vault CSI, HTTP app routing, OMS agent
- ✅ **Monitoring & Alerts** - Create Azure Monitor metric alerts
- ✅ **Managed Identities** - Create and manage user-assigned identities
- ✅ **Role Assignments** - Assign RBAC roles to identities and principals
- ✅ **Deletion Protection** - Optional management lock on the AKS cluster
- ✅ **Cost Controls** - Support autoscaling and Spot node pools

## Usage

### Call from another repository

Point `source` at this repo and the path under it (`//Azure/AKS`). Pin **`ref` to a tag or commit** in production, not a branch that can change.

```hcl
module "aks" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/saurabhrsahu/terraform-modules.git//Azure/AKS?ref=main"
  # Use ?ref=v1.0.0 (or a commit SHA) once you tag releases
  # ...same inputs as in Basic Usage below
}
```

The **root** module where you call this must configure the **AzureRM** provider and authentication. This module only declares it needs `hashicorp/azurerm` and `hashicorp/time`.

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    azurerm = {
      source  = "hashicorp/azurerm"
      version = ">= 4.0.0, < 5.0.0"
    }
    time = {
      source  = "hashicorp/time"
      version = ">= 0.9.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "azurerm" {
  features {}
}
```

`provider "time"` is optional; the default `time` provider is enough for this module.

### Basic Usage

```hcl
module "aks" {
  source = "../../modules/Azure/AKS"

  resource_group_name = "my-rg"
  location            = "eastus"
  cluster_name        = "my-aks"

  default_node_pool = {
    name           = "system"
    vm_size        = "Standard_D2s_v3"
    vnet_subnet_id = "/subscriptions/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/resourceGroups/my-rg/providers/Microsoft.Network/virtualNetworks/my-vnet/subnets/aks-subnet"
    node_count     = 2
  }

  additional_node_pools = {
    "userpool1" = {
      name                = "userpool1"
      vm_size             = "Standard_D4s_v3"
      node_count          = 1
      enable_auto_scaling = true
      min_count           = 1
      max_count           = 3
      priority            = "Regular"
    }
  }

  common_tags = {
    environment = "dev"
    team        = "platform"
  }
}
```

## Inputs

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|------|---------|:--------:|
| `resource_group_name` | Resource group for the AKS cluster | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `location` | Azure region | `string` | `"eastus"` | no |
| `cluster_name` | AKS cluster name | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `default_node_pool` | System/primary node pool config | `object` | n/a | yes |
| `additional_node_pools` | Map of additional node pools | `map(object)` | `{}` | no |
| `private_cluster_enabled` | Enable private AKS control plane | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `api_server_authorized_ip_ranges` | Authorized CIDRs for API server | `list(string)` | `[]` | no |
| `network_plugin` | AKS network plugin (`azure`/`kubenet`) | `string` | `"azure"` | no |
| `enable_oms_agent` | Enable Container Insights OMS agent | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `log_analytics_workspace_id` | Log Analytics workspace resource ID | `string` | `null` | no |
| `user_assigned_identities` | Map of user-assigned managed identities | `map(object)` | `{}` | no |
| `metric_alerts` | Map of Azure Monitor metric alerts | `map(object)` | `{}` | no |

## Outputs

| Name | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `cluster` | Core attributes of the AKS cluster |
| `cluster_name` | Name of the AKS cluster |
| `cluster_id` | Resource ID of the AKS cluster |
| `cluster_fqdn` | Public or private FQDN of the cluster |
| `kube_admin_config_raw` | Raw admin kubeconfig (sensitive) |
| `node_pools` | Information about additional node pools |
| `user_assigned_identities` | Created managed identities |
| `metric_alerts` | Created metric alerts |
| `connection_info` | Azure CLI command to fetch kubeconfig |
| `security_info` | Security-related module settings |

## Requirements

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| terraform | >= 1.3.0 |
| azurerm | >= 4.0.0, < 5.0.0 |
| time | >= 0.9.0 |

